<subSubSection pageId="58" pageNumber="59" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="58.[189,454,1661,1687]" box="[189,454,1661,1687]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,454,1661,1687]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,454,1661,1687]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="58.[189,1399,1708,1877]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bigot" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[189,578,1708,1734]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indiana" subGenus="Endoiasimyia">
<emphasis box="[189,300,1708,1734]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Cheilosia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[315,474,1708,1734]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Endoiasimyia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[490,578,1708,1734]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">indiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares the diagnostic characters of eye and face with pilosity, a plumose arista and proepisternum of propleuron with a dorso-lateral spur with other members of the subgenus. Wing with faint brownish-black cloud from about mid of discal cell to wing tip. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bigot" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[1137,1399,1779,1805]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indiana" subGenus="Endoiasimyia">
<emphasis box="[1137,1249,1779,1805]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Cheilosia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1266,1292,1780,1805]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">E.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1309,1399,1779,1805]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">indiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other members of the subgenus by scutum lacking brown pollinose vittae anterior and posterior to transverse suture.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
